### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/

###
### ── BOOKS ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Get all books
GET http://localhost:5000/api/books

### Get a single book (id 1 = The Hobbit from seed data)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/books/1

### Get a book that doesn't exist (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/books/999

### Create a new book
POST http://localhost:5000/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Name of the Wind",
  "author": "Patrick Rothfuss",
  "isbn": "978-0756404741"
}

### Create a book with missing fields (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "No Author Book"
}

### Update a book (id 3 = The Night Circus)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/books/3
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Night Circus",
  "author": "Erin Morgenstern",
  "isbn": "978-0385534635"
}

### Delete a book that has NO active loans (id 3 = The Night Circus, not loaned)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/books/3

### Delete a book that IS on loan (id 1 = The Hobbit, on loan to Marie — expect 400)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/books/1

###
### ── PEOPLE ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Get all people
GET http://localhost:5000/api/people

### Get a single person (id 1 = Marie Tremblay)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/people/3

### Create a new person
POST http://localhost:5000/api/people
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Isabelle Roy"
}

### Create a duplicate person (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/people
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Marie Tremblay"
}

### Create a person with no name (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/people
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###
### ── LOANS ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Get all active loans
GET http://localhost:5000/api/loans

### Get all loans for Marie (person id 1)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/loans/person/1

### Create a new loan (Project Hail Mary = book 4, Sophie = person 3)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "book_id": 4,
  "person_id": 3,
  "borrowed_date": "2026-03-28"
}

### Try to loan a book already on loan (book 1 = The Hobbit — expect 400)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/loans
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "book_id": 1,
  "person_id": 3,
  "borrowed_date": "2026-03-28"
}

### Mark loan as returned (loan id 2 = Lucas/Dune)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/loans/2/return
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "returned_date": "2026-03-28"
}

### Try to return an already-returned loan (expect 404)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/loans/2/return
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "returned_date": "2026-03-28"
}